# Engine WASM: the GAE image carries exactly one copy of each artifact.
# The full build stays at src/engine/core/libsimlin.wasm (the server loads
# it via node_modules/@simlin/engine). The browser build is excluded here
# because rsbuild already bundled a hashed copy into public/static/wasm/;
# uploading the source artifact too would ship it twice. The .raw files are
# build.sh's wasm-opt change-detection cache and never load at runtime.
/src/engine/core/libsimlin-browser.wasm
/src/engine/core/*.raw

# Untracked scratch directories. .gcloudignore does NOT import .gitignore
# (intentionally, so that gitignored build output like src/*/lib and
# src/engine/core/libsimlin.wasm still uploads), so these never-tracked dirs
# would otherwise be uploaded and blow past GAE Standard's 10,000-file/version
# cap. Each path below is verified to hold zero git-tracked files; excluding
# them cannot affect any source or build output. Root-anchored for precision.
/third_party/
/.venv/
/.venv-pysimlin/
/env/
/.hypothesis/
/.pytest_cache/
/simlin/
/playwright-report/
/test-results/
/src/pysimlin/venv/
/src/pysimlin/.venv/
/src/pysimlin/build/
/src/pysimlin/dist/

# The staged-deploy output dir (scripts/build-deploy-staging.mjs). It is left
# in place after `pnpm deploy:web:staged` so a --no-promote smoke test can
# inspect exactly what was uploaded. Exclude it here so a SUBSEQUENT fallback
# `pnpm deploy:web` -- which uploads from the repo root -- does not re-upload
# the ~28 MB staged artifact (its own app.yaml carrying the session secret, the
# vendored packages, lockfile, and public bundle) or burn the 10k-file budget.
# The staged deploy itself uploads from deploy-staging/ with its own
# .gcloudignore, so this root entry does not affect it.
/deploy-staging/
